---
import Alert from "../components/Alert.astro";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../styles/prose.scss";
---

<Layout title="WikiStats - About">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-4 break-words w-full prose">
        <h1 class="!mb-0">About</h1>
        <p class="!m-0">
            If you have any questions, which are not answered here, or
            suggestions, feel free to contact <a href="https://gaareth.com">
                me
            </a>.
        </p>

        <section>
            <h2 id="data">Data</h2>
            <div>
                <p>
                    The data is collected from the wikimedia dumps at:
                    <a href="https://dumps.wikimedia.org/">
                        https://dumps.wikimedia.org/
                    </a> or one of their mirrors. These dumps contain <a
                        href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Database_dump">
                        sql dumps
                    </a> of various wikipedia <a
                        href="https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Category:MediaWiki_database_tables">
                        tables
                    </a>. I currently use the <a
                        href="https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Manual:page_table">
                        page
                    </a>, <a
                        href="https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Manual:pagelinks_table">
                        pagelinks
                    </a>, and
                    <a
                        href="https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Manual:Linktarget_table">
                        linktarget
                    </a> tables to generate the stats.
                </p>

                <p>
                    <a
                        href="https://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Data_dumps/Dump_frequency">
                        Frequency
                    </a>: The dumps appear to be updated every month at the 20th
                    and the first. Hence the dump dates are typically yyyyMMDD
                    and end with 01 or 20. You can read more about it here: <a
                        href="https://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Data_dumps">
                        https://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Data_dumps
                    </a>
                </p>
            </div>

            <h3 id="data-validity">Validity</h3>
            <p>
                The pagelinks and linktarget table don't always accurately
                reflect the actual links on the webpage. For example: the <a
                    href="Nati il 21 aprile">
                    https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nati_il_21_aprile
                </a> page is frequently updated. The link to <a
                    href="https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wesllem">
                    Wesllem
                </a> was removed on the <a
                    href="https://it.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Nati_il_21_aprile&oldid=147034440">
                    second october at 1am
                </a> and added back at <a
                    href="https://it.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Nati_il_21_aprile&oldid=147036038">
                    8am
                </a>. However it was present at the <a
                    href="https://it.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Nati_il_21_aprile&oldid=146885011">
                    24th september
                </a>
                (See: <a
                    href="https://it.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Nati_il_21_aprile&action=history">
                    history
                </a>). It appears that as a result the 20251001 dumpdate does
                not contain this link. Which makes sense as the corresponding
                table dump was finished at <a
                    href="https://dumps.wikimedia.org/itwiki/20251001/">
                    2025-10-02 04:51:21.
                </a>
            </p>

            <Alert type="error" className="text-xl">
                The results shown here may not always fully reflect the current
                links online, especially for websites that are frequently
                updated.
            </Alert>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Accessibility</h2>
            <p>
                Im trying to improve the accessibility of this website and make
                it mostly usable even without javascript. If you find something
                which works suboptimal please don't hesitate to inform me.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Technical</h2>
            <p>
                The frontend is built using <a href="https://astro.build/">
                    AstroJS
                </a> and is mostly static. For the interactive parts <a
                    href="https://www.solidjs.com/">
                    SolidJS
                </a> is used. The (network) graph visualizations use <a
                    href="https://www.sigmajs.org/">
                    Sigma.js
                </a> in the background. And the charts use <a
                    href="https://www.chartjs.org/">
                    Chart.js
                </a>
            </p>
            <p>
                Finding the shortest path at <a href="/wiki/path">
                    shortest path
                </a> works using a bidirectional breadth first search. In comparison
                to a normal bfs this drastically improves performance. Credits <a
                    href="https://www.sixdegreesofwikipedia.com/">
                    https://www.sixdegreesofwikipedia.com/
                </a> for this idea.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Attribution</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    This project uses icons from <a
                        href="https://github.com/google/material-design-icons">
                        Material Symbols
                    </a>
                    by google, licensed under the <a href="Apache License 2.0">
                        Apache License 2.0
                    </a>. The Logo uses a modified search icon.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            You can find the sourcecode at <a
                href="https://github.com/Gaareth/WikiStats/">
                GitHub
            </a>
        </section>
    </div>
</Layout>
